{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d388cf45-4290-4b28-9704-9ddc408f3baf","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nHot reload with `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` works through the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is an executable. `dotnet run` launches that executable and keeps it alive to watch for file changes.\n\n`dotnet test` runs tests and exits — it doesn't support the hot reload loop.\n\nSo your workflow is:\n\n```bash\n# Set the env var (you said you already did this)\nexport TESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED=1\n\n# Then launch with dotnet run\ndotnet run\n```\n\nThe runner will execute your tests, then watch for source changes and automatically re-run on save.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f6b203c5-534d-4011-acf6-b87e50d9c9f0","outputTokens":161,"requestId":"BD08:2F6EDC:1DE944E:2175F2B:6A07C0EA"},"id":"0b1e62ce-83cc-4219-a46c-d88f61abf492","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:57:23.337Z","parentId":"caa4bf25-b560-4207-a66d-6d3e7b1cb11b"}
